$ Graphviz: attribute types

→ tools/Graphviz/attributes[Attributes] are key-value pairs. An attribute key has *one* type. This type specifies the range of values that can be assigned to the key.

table { ll
  addDouble   ☰ A double with an optional prefix `+`
  addPoint    ☰ A point with an optional prefix `+`
  → tools/Graphviz/attributes/types/arrowType  ☰ 
  bool        ☰ 
  clusterMode ☰ `local`, `global`, `none`
  color       ☰ `#rrggbb`, `#rrggbbaa`. `h.hhh s.sss v.vvv`, `red`
  colorList   ☰ A colon separated list of weighted color values
  dirType     ☰ `forward`, `back`, `both` or `none`
  double      ☰ 
  → tools/Graphviz/labels/escString ☰ Replace escape sequences in strings.
  int         ☰ 
